title: Claude Monet Cliff Walk at Pourville Poster
description:
Poster developed from Claude Monet’s Cliff Walk at Pourville, 1882, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Claude Monet (French, 1840-1926) is one of the greatest and most enduringly popular artists of all time. Monet's work went through many thematic and stylistic phases during his long career; always his goal was to capture the impression on the viewer's eye and record the visual sensation of light and color that guided his brush. 

  • Dimensions:  32 in. x 26 in. 
  • Premium Cardstock.
